## 📊 Sample Airports

* DEL (Delhi)
* MUM (Mumbai)
* BLR (Bangalore)
* HYD (Hyderabad)
* CCU (Kolkata)
* DXB (Dubai)
* SIN (Singapore)
* LHR (London)

---

## 💡 How It Works

* Airports are modeled as nodes in a graph.
* Routes between them are edges with weights.
* Weight = Distance + Weather Penalty + Congestion Factor.
* Selected algorithm computes the best route.

---

## 📸 Output

* GUI displays selected route and cost.
* Graph visualization highlights optimal path.

---

## ⚠️ Notes

* Results may vary due to random weather and congestion factors.
* BFS does not guarantee minimum cost (only minimum stops).

